{
  "stem": "23641.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I-- because I heard in Szczecin my aunt and uncle, what-- when the Russians came in 19-- 1939, they came to Wlodawa.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they said to the people that we should go-- everybody should go and leave Wlodawa, go with them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my aunt and uncle, with my cousin-- they went there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they survived-- they survived the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they went-- they came back from Russia after the war to Szczecin.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I saw-- I went to them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then I went back, back and forth, until we decided we're going to leave Wlodawa for good.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We left Wlodawa, with my uncle and my aunt.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I think my aunt had a girl born, and I helped her going-- we went to Szczecin, with the idea we're not going to stay in Szczecin with the idea that we were going to go to Germany.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And from Germany, we're going to emigrate to some other country.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was what happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we stayed there a while in Szczecin.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And later on, somebody-- I don't know, my uncle arranged it-- that they took us with a truck over the border, the Polish border.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we arrived in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So-- and I wind up in a DP camp in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Schlachtensee.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I stayed there until the-- until the blockade-- in Schlachtensee until the blockade-- the Russians put the blockade on Berlin.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the Americans took out the camps from Schlachtensee.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they always settled them to first Germany.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I came to the-- and I came to a camp in West Germany named Wasseralfingen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then from Wasseralfingen, they liquidated Wasseralfingen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And from Wasseralfingen-- while being in Wasseralfingen, somebody made a matchmaker for me.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
